tables.table_title: Distributions of $\mathrm{E}_{\mathrm{T}}^{\mathrm{miss}}$ in $SR^{\mathrm{Z}}_{\mathrm{1A}}$ for events passing all the SR requirements except those on the variable being plotted (the requirements are indicated by the arrows). The contributions from all SM backgrounds are shown after the background fit described in Section 5 of the paper; the hashed bands represent the total uncertainty. The `Others' category contains the contributions from $\mathrm{t\bar{t}\ h}$, $\mathrm{t\bar{t}\ W}$, $\mathrm{t\bar{t}\ WW}$, $\mathrm{t\bar{t}\ t}$, $\mathrm{t\bar{t}\ t\bar{t}}$, Wh, and Zh production. The ''FNP'' category represents the background from fake or non-prompt leptons. The expected distributions for selected signal models are also shown as dashed lines. The last bin in each figure contains the overflow.

Distributions of $\mathrm{E_{T}^{miss}}$ significance in $\mathrm{SR_{1A}^{h}}$ for events passing all the SR requirements except those on the variable being plotted (the requirements are indicated by the arrows). The contributions from all SM backgrounds are shown after the background fit described in Section 5 of the paper; the hashed bands represent the total uncertainty. The ''Higgs'' category contains the contributions from gluon--gluon fusion, vector-boson fusion, Wh, Zh and $\mathrm{t\bar{t}}$ h production. The ''Others'' category contains the contributions from $t\bar{t}\ WW$, $t\bar{t} WZ$, $t\bar{t}\ t$ and $t\bar{t}\ t\bar{t}$ production. The expected distributions for selected signal models are also shown as dashed lines. The last bin in each figure contains the overflow.

The ''Others'' category contains the contributions from $t\bar{t}\ WW$, $t\bar{t} WZ$, $t\bar{t}\ t$ and $t\bar{t}\ t\bar{t}$ production. The expected distributions for selected signal models are also shown as dashed lines. The last bin in each figure contains the overflow.

Observed exclusion limit at $95\%$ CL on the masses of the $\tilde{t}_{1}$ and $\tilde{\chi}_2^0$, for a fixed m($\tilde{\chi}_1^0$) = $0$ GeV, assuming B($\tilde{\chi}_{2}^{0}$ $\rightarrow$ Z$\tilde{\chi}_{1}^{0}$) = $0.5$ and B($\tilde{\chi}_{2}^{0}$ $\rightarrow$ h$\tilde{\chi}_{1}^{0}$) = $0.5$. The limit is given for the central value of the signal cross-section and does not include the effect of the theoretical uncertainties in the signal cross-section.
